r> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/12/02 1:06:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Undead Bard and spawned Trak</span><hr size=1> Our guild's highest level bard is only this last step away from her epic.  No one in the guild though has ever done Trak.  From what I understand, for Bard epic the spawned Trak is lower lvl and easier than real trak, similar to VS/VSR in KC.<br>
<br>
so, if any of you could share some of your knowledge of this fight, I'd be happy to learn.<br>
<br>
How hard does UDB/Spawned Trak hit for?<br>
<br>
Are either mobs slowable?<br>
<br>
What procs or aoes are there? (poison I understand).<br>
<br>
How much damage does the aoe inflict?<br>
<br>
How many hps?  How is aggro control?  <br>
<br>
What size raid force is needed?<br>
<br>
We can do VSR piece of cake.  We can put ~3 clerics, 2 shammies. 2 chanters. 2 bards, 3-4 tanks, 2 rogues, 2 monks, and the odd necro/druid/beastlord type classes together without much trouble.<br>
<br>
Any and all info you are willing to share is greatly appreciated. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=464869">Nyssah</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=suretass>suretass</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/13/02 6:11:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Undead Bard and spawned Trak</span><hr size=1> My Bard is also at this stage but the biggest problem I have seen is that now Trak spawns about every 3 days and no-one on Saryrn seems to kill him anymore. As the UDB is KoS to Trak he is killed on spawn by Trak and hence he is never up.<br>
I have heard that the UDB will sometimes be up on Server up and if you are quick you can get there before Trak pops, this is probably the best bet.<br>
<br>
As for Trak, I didn't fight him yet so others here can probably give good advice. I did however look into it for my Bard and I Think he is basically the same as the real think but just doesn't drop normal loot. Hits are 600 ish I believe but the Poison AoE is a real pain so necro's/bards really help. Also make sure you get everyone cured after so that the raid force doesn't die looking at his corpse.<br>
<br>
I think the pull is easier as you get to clear the lair with Trak being up and all the melee can be ready at his Spawn point when you spawn him.<br>
<br>
Like I said, you will prolly get better advice but this is the info I picked up so far.<br>
<br>
I also heard its possible for the Real Trak to pop while fighting the spawned one though kind of unlikely. Would be nasty if it happened though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilzadikandinsky>KilzadiKandinsky</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/13/02 7:52:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Undead Bard and spawned Trak</span><hr size=1> Trak and spawned trak are the same. same AoE, same hitpoints, same resists. load up on poision resist gear, my first raid down there didn't and when good ole' trak started running(lotsa people low on hp due to superubermega DoT) he agroed the juggs and they slaughtered us, but not before our bard looted the epic bit and the bp off trakky (ranger. bah!) trak is a do or die fight you either get him dead in 15-20 seconds flat or you're dead; load up on wizards for this, a wizards short term dps when dumping his mana bar into a 32k mob is far far superior to a rogue on such a short fight. i.e 2  bs's for the rogue thats 2k damage(maximum, considering good double attack rolls) from bsing alone. but a wizard can cast 3 sunstrikes in that time. <br>
<br>
so my strat is now to 1 set a balanced group to keep the juggs clear around the bridge/ protector/reets area, have everybody load up on poision resist gear (i now keep a spare set of BD gear just in case someone forgets), once you have your force ready for hand in to the UDB. have all melee face towards traks spawn point. when trak spawns surround him. DO NOT PUSH HIM INTO A WALL, he can and will gate. once dead, loot up do the rolls; grab your juggs group(if they dont' want to stay and kill juggs some more) evac out, simple. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=turomtoesmasher>Turom Toesmasher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 454<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/13/02 9:31:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.gaiahealing.com/everquest/turom_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Undead Bard and spawned Trak</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>trak is a do or die fight you either get him dead in 15-20 seconds flat or you're dead<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Actually this is not quite true.  I don't think I've ever been on a Trak raid that only lasted 15-20 seconds and I've killed him many times.<br>
