I'd agree that the faster you kill him the better, but 15-20 is a bit misleading. <p><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><center><tr><td valign="top" align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11741" target="dorfsex"><img border="0" src="http://www.gaiahealing.com/everquest/turom_sig.jpg"></a><br><b><table style='filter: alpha(opacity=100, finishopacity=50, style=3, startx=85, finishx=20, starty=0, finishy=0')><font color=white face=verdana, arial, helvetica><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11741" target="dorfsex"><font color=white><p align="center">Turom Toesmasher</font></a><font color=red> .o. </font><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior" target="dorfsex"><font color=white>61 Dwarven Warlord</font></a><br><a href="http://pub43.ezboard.com/b7thhammer" target="dorfsex"><font color="white">The Seventh Hammer</font></a></table></td></tr></b></center></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xorgogorgonzolo>Xorgo Gorgonzolo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/13/02 10:38:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Undead Bard and spawned Trak</span><hr size=1> Once I was camping Juggs for spells in trak lair and OS zone crashed.  When it came back up UDB was up immediately so I can confirm hes up on server/zone start.  Trak spawns anytime in a 1 day window from server start so there should be some time to get UDB if you go early.  I remember our last bard epic fight we went for that UDB about 10 hrs after server start and I had a bad feeling about Trak crashing the party. Sure enough, he popped about 5 min after we killed the UDB-spawned one.  But our bard got her epic piece.  And yes hes same as normal Trak, only advantage you have is everyone is there ready for him instead of streaming in from the broken bridge area.<br>
<br>
Some Trak advice:<br>
If your first time I would go with 5-6 groups.  He hits for 600ish and his AE dot is about 1k-1200 up front and 150 hp /tick dot.   I dont know if hes slowable -- and by time debuffs would be in and slow attempt made he better be half dead anyway.  If you fight him towards the entrance to lair he can gate to the back of lair and he regens a good chunk of his hp back.  If you fight UDB where he spawns I dont think he'll gate.<br>
<br>
Go full offensive on him.  Have a couple main tanks -- and if possible a COTH mage to bring them back from trak touch to shrooms before they die.  Otherwise be ready to go summon from zone or something.  Cleric's Word of Restoration is great spell for the fight.  After fight have poisoned folks stand and cured folks sit and everyone that can cure poison chain casting on those still under its effect.  UDB after turnin himself is a wuss like the human zordak -- save mana for trak.<br>
<br>
<br>
Good luck <p>Xorgo Gorgonzolo &lt;Anlah'Shok&gt;</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xorgogorgonzolo>Xorgo Gorgonzolo</A> at: 12/13/02 10:54:09 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gallerus>Gallerus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/13/02 10:50:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1597.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Undead Bard and spawned Trak</span><hr size=1> undead bard trak can drop 1 bp instead of 2 that trak usually drops &amp; also udb trak dont drop vp key teeth.<br>
